---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Dongho Lee Real Estate"
  description="Privacy Policy for Dongho Lee Real Estate, including how contact form and website inquiry information may be collected and used."
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <header>
      <p class="page-kicker">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: July 18, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="legal-content">
      <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          Dongho Lee Real Estate respects your privacy. This policy explains how information submitted through this website may be collected, used, and protected when you contact us about real estate services in Ontario.
        </p>
        <p>
          Privacy Contact: Dongho Lee 이동호, Broker, REALTOR®, HomeLife Frontier Realty Inc., Brokerage, 7620 Yonge Street, Suite 400, Thornhill, Ontario L4J 1V9. Email: <a href="mailto:contact@donlee.realtor">contact@donlee.realtor</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Name, email address, phone number, preferred area, and message details submitted through the contact form.</li>
          <li>Basic technical information such as browser type, device type, pages visited, and referral source when analytics or hosting logs are available.</li>
          <li>Information you voluntarily provide by phone, email, text message, or consultation request.</li>
          <li>Lead source, landing page, referral source, expected transaction timeframe, and the date and context of any marketing consent.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>
          Information is used to respond to inquiries, prepare for consultations, provide real estate guidance, improve website content, and maintain records related to client communication.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information. Information may be shared only when needed to provide requested services, comply with legal obligations, or work with professional service providers involved in a real estate matter.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact Form</h2>
        <p>
          When you submit the contact form, your message is transmitted so we can respond directly. Please avoid sending highly sensitive personal, financial, or confidential documents through the website form.
        </p>
        <p>
          Contact form submissions may be processed by a third-party form, email delivery, hosting, or security provider solely for transmitting, protecting, and managing your inquiry.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data Retention And Security</h2>
        <p>
          We keep inquiry and communication records only as long as reasonably necessary for business, legal, and service purposes. Reasonable safeguards are used, but no website or email transmission can be guaranteed to be completely secure.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Marketing Messages And Consent</h2>
        <p>
          Consent to receive market updates or other commercial electronic messages is optional and separate
          from consent to process a specific inquiry. We record the source, date, and scope of express consent.
          Commercial electronic messages identify the sender and provide a working way to unsubscribe. You may
          withdraw consent at any time by using the unsubscribe method in a message or emailing
          <a href="mailto:contact@donlee.realtor">contact@donlee.realtor</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>CRM And Follow-up Records</h2>
        <p>
          Inquiry information may be stored in a customer relationship management system to track the inquiry
          source, requested services, consent status, and appropriate follow-up. An inquiry submitted without
          marketing consent is not treated as a general newsletter subscription.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your Choices</h2>
        <p>
          You may request access, correction, or deletion of your personal information where legally available. To make a privacy request, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@donlee.realtor">contact@donlee.realtor</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
